MOST families do not deal with anger directly. This results in children being unable to handle the emotion in a healthy and appropriate manner.When parents deal with anger correctly, they limit the strength of the feeling and prevent destructive behaviour.What is anger? It is a feeling of displeasure, irritation or dislike that is a reaction to frustration, threat, loss, trauma, sadness or criticism.What to teach a child:Create a peaceful environment in the home and in the child.Listen attentively to them and encourage self-expression.Do not use labels such as &ldquo;bad kid&rdquo; or &ldquo;ufuze umzali ngokusa&rdquo;.Laughter dilutes anger and is a great distraction for kids.Dealing with anger gives you the freedom to live a life filled with joy. Holding on to anger compromises your future aspirations.